01:55.040 --> 01:59.000
(MUSIC BLARES)

02:16.880 --> 02:18.840
(DOORBELL RINGS)

02:20.120 --> 02:23.360
Samantha.
Hiya. How is she?

02:24.680 --> 02:25.840
Bright.

02:26.960 --> 02:27.960
Bright.

02:29.080 --> 02:31.760
Ah, here she is.

02:31.760 --> 02:34.240
How are you, Sarah?
Still here.

02:38.440 --> 02:40.080
Are you ready to get back into it?

02:41.400 --> 02:43.440
We left off so suddenly last time.

02:43.440 --> 02:45.040
Coffee and strudel?

02:45.040 --> 02:46.520
Ooh, thank you, Leah.

02:46.520 --> 02:48.640
Could you turn the radio off,
please?

02:51.240 --> 02:56.440
So, how is the writing going?
Good. I'm well into it.

02:57.680 --> 03:00.680
Um, I couldn't find anything
in the records

03:00.680 --> 03:02.240
about the body you mentioned.

03:02.240 --> 03:04.160
Body?

03:04.160 --> 03:07.480
Before we stopped,
you mentioned a body in the river.

03:07.480 --> 03:09.400
I couldn't find any record of it.

03:13.040 --> 03:15.880
You don't remember?
Body? No.

03:15.880 --> 03:18.800
So, where were we, apart from that?

03:18.800 --> 03:21.120
James had just started
his treatment.

03:21.120 --> 03:22.640
His torture.

03:26.320 --> 03:28.400
I can't believe
they actually used to do that.

03:28.400 --> 03:31.800
And worse.
All in the name of normalcy.

03:32.880 --> 03:35.960
How did Gran take it?
Poor Olivia.

03:35.960 --> 03:38.640
Soon with so many lies of her own.

03:47.440 --> 03:49.680
But that was later.

03:49.680 --> 03:53.760
Anna.
She was moving out to be with Gino.

03:53.760 --> 03:55.920
Ah, yes. Her new life.

03:56.960 --> 04:01.600
Such a confusing time,
losing a child and gaining a father.

04:01.600 --> 04:04.240
When did she find out
it was Jack Duncan?

04:04.240 --> 04:07.160
Oh, it was quite some time
before that happened.

04:08.320 --> 04:10.760
She had quite enough
to contend with as it was.

04:17.680 --> 04:20.480
(HORN HONKS)

04:20.480 --> 04:21.800
Before I forget,

04:21.800 --> 04:25.680
you didn't say what Roy felt
about you leaving the farm.

04:48.680 --> 04:50.680
How did Roy feel?
I heard you, dear.

04:52.040 --> 04:53.280
He was happy for me.

05:14.440 --> 05:15.960
Ready?

05:15.960 --> 05:17.440
Yeah.

05:18.760 --> 05:20.360
Now...

05:21.760 --> 05:23.360
..where shall we pick it all up?

05:24.960 --> 05:31.080
Carolyn, so long the black sheep,
so much a part of the future.

05:31.080 --> 05:33.240
I know it's out of the blue...
JACK: Stop.

05:33.240 --> 05:34.920
..but there are...
Wait!

05:37.320 --> 05:38.520
We had a child?

05:40.320 --> 05:41.960
You left me.
I had no choice.

05:41.960 --> 05:43.480
I don't see you for 20 years...
I know.

05:43.480 --> 05:45.040
..and you turn up like this.
I'm sorry.

05:45.040 --> 05:47.880
Our daughter?
I'm trying to do the right thing.

05:47.880 --> 05:49.600
For who?
Both of us.

05:49.600 --> 05:50.600
Right.

05:50.600 --> 05:53.840
There were reasons I never told you,
but I am trying to fix it.

05:55.680 --> 05:58.880
Who is she? Where is she?
I...I...

05:58.880 --> 06:00.760
Well, is she here? Overseas?
I can't tell you.

06:00.760 --> 06:01.880
Why?
Not yet.

06:01.880 --> 06:04.320
Why not?!
It's difficult.

06:04.320 --> 06:06.480
So, why now?

06:07.480 --> 06:10.400
She's just found out about me...

06:11.400 --> 06:13.760
..and it's only a matter of time
before she asks about her father.

06:15.240 --> 06:17.120
I wanted to give you a choice.

06:19.400 --> 06:24.520
If she does ask, what do I say?
I want to do the right thing.

06:24.520 --> 06:27.400
You may not want this. I don't know.

06:27.400 --> 06:31.120
I could say you died in the war
if you'd rather.

06:31.120 --> 06:32.240
(DOOR OPENS)

06:32.240 --> 06:35.600
Excuse me, Doctor.
Mrs Danthers needs you.

06:36.880 --> 06:38.360
I'm coming.

06:40.120 --> 06:42.240
Should I wait? Jack!

06:44.960 --> 06:46.240
Where are you staying?

06:46.240 --> 06:49.640
The Ash Park guest cottage.
No-one knows I'm here.

06:50.800 --> 06:52.160
Please come.

07:02.880 --> 07:05.160
Doris Collins, please, Mildred.

07:07.680 --> 07:09.880
Such a tasteful setting.

07:11.600 --> 07:13.000
Thank you.
Thank you, Amy.

07:14.880 --> 07:17.200
Please do help yourself,
Mrs Collins.

07:18.440 --> 07:20.400
So very good of you to hurry over.

07:20.400 --> 07:23.600
When you mentioned
I may be of assistance,

07:23.600 --> 07:25.400
if there's anything I can do...

07:25.400 --> 07:27.840
Well, you've heard the news,
I assume.

07:29.160 --> 07:30.400
About Anna.

07:31.880 --> 07:34.960
I make it my business
never to listen to tittle-tattle.

07:34.960 --> 07:37.640
Oh, that they were more like you.

07:38.800 --> 07:40.480
Is there a problem?

07:40.480 --> 07:42.120
Oh, not at all, no.

07:42.120 --> 07:44.160
Anna's moved in with the Polettis
for a period.

07:44.160 --> 07:45.480
But they're Italian.

07:45.480 --> 07:47.520
Unorthodox.
Unorthodox.

07:47.520 --> 07:50.480
She has her heart set on Italy
for the northern summer.

07:50.480 --> 07:52.240
She and Carla are very close

07:52.240 --> 07:54.160
so what better way
to learn the language?

07:54.160 --> 07:55.440
I see.

07:55.440 --> 07:57.600
But there is an unmarried son
in the house

07:57.600 --> 08:00.600
and baser minds may see gossip
where there is none.

08:00.600 --> 08:02.280
No!
Sadly.

08:03.680 --> 08:06.680
As a mother of sorts
to two young girls,

08:06.680 --> 08:08.960
I understand the importance
of protecting their reputation.

08:08.960 --> 08:10.960
If I hear any scurrilous rumours...

08:10.960 --> 08:12.200
I knew I could count on you.

08:13.160 --> 08:15.040
Dear Mrs Bligh.

08:18.040 --> 08:21.400
And then, of course,
we have Miss Adams moving in here.

08:21.400 --> 08:23.880
Ah, yes, indeed. After the wedding.

08:23.880 --> 08:25.600
Before.

08:27.960 --> 08:29.800
GIRL: Mamma,
you should see Anna's dresses.

08:29.800 --> 08:31.800
They don't fit in the wardrobe.

08:31.800 --> 08:33.520
Mamma says
three dresses are enough -

08:33.520 --> 08:35.480
two for everyday and one for church.

08:35.480 --> 08:37.400
For a farmer's wife, it is true.

08:38.400 --> 08:40.240
Tomatoes.
Can Anna come?

08:40.240 --> 08:41.760
Anna is helping me.

08:41.760 --> 08:43.960
You can't cook?
I will learn.

08:43.960 --> 08:46.240
I will teach you
as my mamma taught me.

08:46.240 --> 08:47.800
This is a special meal.

08:47.800 --> 08:49.960
Pollo - chicken.
Oh.

08:49.960 --> 08:51.760
(CHICKENS CLUCK)

08:51.760 --> 08:54.320
First, we kill. Then, we pluck.

09:13.680 --> 09:16.040
I shall be your eyes and ears.

09:16.040 --> 09:18.680
Well, I'm most grateful.

09:18.680 --> 09:22.160
Norman will drive you back to town.
Oh, how kind.

09:25.680 --> 09:27.160
The hospital, please, Norman.

09:29.760 --> 09:33.240
Oh, and give my regards
to Miss Carolyn.

09:33.240 --> 09:34.480
Carolyn?

09:34.480 --> 09:37.040
I saw her at the station.
She has luggage.

09:37.040 --> 09:39.960
I assume she's staying.
Is she not staying?

09:39.960 --> 09:41.760
Of course.
Indeed.

09:41.760 --> 09:44.120
I shall be sure
to give her your regards.

09:44.120 --> 09:45.240
Norman.

09:51.960 --> 09:56.240
How is it so far?
I plucked a chicken.

09:56.240 --> 09:59.160
Will wonders never cease?
I hope not.

10:00.120 --> 10:03.040
I'm allowed to worry.
That's what fathers do.

10:03.040 --> 10:04.960
Yes.

10:04.960 --> 10:07.160
What?
Nothing.

10:08.760 --> 10:11.240
Is it your grandmother?
No, it's not that.

10:11.240 --> 10:12.320
Then what?

10:14.600 --> 10:19.280
Anna, after what I've agreed to,
I hope I've earned your trust.

10:21.120 --> 10:22.600
You and I...

10:24.120 --> 10:25.160
..we're...

10:30.040 --> 10:31.960
Whatever you felt you had to do,

10:31.960 --> 10:34.960
whatever lies you told,
I forgive you.

10:34.960 --> 10:37.000
You're still my little girl...

10:38.320 --> 10:39.680
..and you always will be.

11:03.440 --> 11:05.560
Do you skulk into town often?

11:06.840 --> 11:09.080
(PHONE RINGS)

11:09.080 --> 11:10.560
Sorry.

11:13.000 --> 11:14.280
I have to take this.

11:14.280 --> 11:16.800
Let's have a break.
Five minutes?

11:16.800 --> 11:20.320
See if you can remember what
you were going to tell me about Roy.

11:22.160 --> 11:23.320
Hi. It's Sam.

11:40.080 --> 11:41.960
Roy, what's the matter?

12:45.974 --> 12:48.694
I thought
our communicating by telephone

12:48.694 --> 12:51.694
was simply
a necessarily evil consequence

12:51.694 --> 12:53.214
of your living in the city.

12:54.254 --> 12:56.614
Clearly,
you simply prefer the separation.

12:56.614 --> 12:58.334
This visit isn't about you.

12:59.494 --> 13:01.094
May I inquire what it is about?

13:02.854 --> 13:05.534
I'm here to meet
my future sister-in-law.

13:07.334 --> 13:10.174
Where Sarah Adams walks,
division follows.

13:10.174 --> 13:13.374
That's exactly the attitude
that encourages skulking.

13:13.374 --> 13:16.294
George seems happier
than he's been in years.

13:16.294 --> 13:18.054
Whilst the family is in splinters.

13:18.054 --> 13:20.414
Blighs are in splinters, mother.
Put down the axe.

13:20.414 --> 13:22.694
Oh, spare me the metaphors.

13:22.694 --> 13:25.774
I'm doing what I must
to protect us all.

13:25.774 --> 13:28.854
From what?
The woman's influence.

13:29.854 --> 13:32.334
You'll end up with no-one
if you're not careful.

13:32.334 --> 13:35.054
Then what's left for you to protect?

13:35.054 --> 13:36.374
Our good name...

13:37.414 --> 13:39.614
..which the rest of you
seem intent on ruining.

13:40.974 --> 13:45.214
So, if you could resist adding fuel
to any flames whilst you're here,

13:45.214 --> 13:46.654
I would appreciate it.

13:48.414 --> 13:49.894
I'll do my best.

14:25.854 --> 14:27.014
You should wash up.

14:35.694 --> 14:37.654
I know it's not...
I'll be in in a sec.

14:41.694 --> 14:43.694
Are you right with what we've done?

14:46.614 --> 14:48.574
We saved more lives
from being ruined.

14:50.614 --> 14:52.094
You know the alternative.

14:58.214 --> 15:00.054
I've done it again, haven't I?

15:02.774 --> 15:05.414
I'm starting to think
you want to tell me.

15:05.414 --> 15:07.774
I do keep rambling back to it.

15:09.854 --> 15:13.414
Talking to you has unearthed
so many ghosts.

15:13.414 --> 15:16.054
I can keep a secret. I promise.

15:17.054 --> 15:20.414
60 years, no-one's known.

15:21.414 --> 15:23.574
There. Off the record.

15:28.974 --> 15:30.294
There was a murder...

15:31.494 --> 15:33.854
..and Roy and I
disposed of the body.

15:35.694 --> 15:37.334
Did Roy kill someone?

15:37.334 --> 15:41.134
Roy? No, no, someone else.
Someone we needed to protect.

15:41.134 --> 15:43.134
Who?

15:45.774 --> 15:47.694
You can't just tell me
about a murder...

15:47.694 --> 15:48.734
Enough!

15:53.014 --> 15:54.814
Let's get back to your grandmother.

16:00.134 --> 16:01.294
Olivia!

16:02.414 --> 16:03.414
Andrew.

16:03.414 --> 16:05.334
What are you doing here?

16:05.334 --> 16:07.654
I'm not sure you're meant
to ask that at the loony bin.

16:08.774 --> 16:11.494
Sorry. Um, I was just passing.

16:11.494 --> 16:14.014
You seem to be heading towards,
not past.

16:15.134 --> 16:17.494
A friend from London.

16:17.494 --> 16:21.894
She lives here now
and she has a nervous complaint.

16:23.134 --> 16:24.574
One tries to be discreet.

16:24.574 --> 16:26.894
I didn't think you had friends
in Australia.

16:27.934 --> 16:29.694
An old school friend.

16:29.694 --> 16:32.054
Well, I'm checking up on father.
He's drying out.

16:32.054 --> 16:34.014
Oh, I didn't...
Look, don't feel uncomfortable.

16:34.014 --> 16:36.934
The lecherous old reprobate has
forfeited his right to discretion.

16:38.454 --> 16:42.614
Well, I won't keep you.
Wish him my best.

16:42.614 --> 16:43.974
What are you doing in the city?

16:43.974 --> 16:49.174
Um...James and I
are spending time here.

16:49.174 --> 16:50.974
A holiday of sorts.

16:50.974 --> 16:52.334
And where's he?

16:52.334 --> 16:54.454
James? At the hotel.

16:56.654 --> 17:00.494
You really should visit Anna,
you know.

17:00.494 --> 17:01.734
She'd love to see you.

17:01.734 --> 17:04.814
Really?
Of course.

17:04.814 --> 17:07.814
Without us at Ash Park,
she'd relish the company.

17:07.814 --> 17:09.854
I have been thinking of her lately.

17:10.973 --> 17:12.013
I won't detain you.

17:13.374 --> 17:14.614
Give James my best.

17:48.214 --> 17:49.934
How are you feeling, my darling?

17:51.374 --> 17:52.494
I think...

17:54.974 --> 17:57.414
I don't know what...

18:01.654 --> 18:03.814
I hate seeing you like this.

18:06.654 --> 18:08.334
Come back to me.

18:11.134 --> 18:12.854
Who are you?

18:14.654 --> 18:17.854
If you don't want
to do this anymore,

18:17.854 --> 18:20.014
you just say.

18:20.014 --> 18:22.534
Do you hear me?

18:22.534 --> 18:26.614
If it gets too much, just say.

18:26.614 --> 18:28.574
Ah, we're awake.

18:28.574 --> 18:30.974
How are we feeling, James?

18:30.974 --> 18:33.374
Foggy.
Mm-hm.

18:33.374 --> 18:36.094
You must be Mrs Bligh.
I'm Dr Wilson.

18:36.094 --> 18:38.454
I oversee James's daily treatment.

18:38.454 --> 18:40.414
I thought Dr Stewart was in charge.

18:40.414 --> 18:43.494
Rest assured,
I work closely with Dr Stewart.

18:43.494 --> 18:46.654
I specialise
in this particular form of deviancy.

18:46.654 --> 18:49.694
His memory still isn't back.

18:49.694 --> 18:51.694
Is that normal?
It is.

18:51.694 --> 18:53.854
Are you ready
for your next treatment, old man?

18:54.814 --> 18:57.054
But he's barely rested
from the last.

18:57.054 --> 18:58.294
Mrs Bligh...

18:58.294 --> 19:01.734
Shouldn't you at least wait
until he's himself again?

19:01.734 --> 19:03.894
Being himself
is precisely the problem.

19:03.894 --> 19:05.654
This is the treatment.

19:05.654 --> 19:07.374
This is what Dr Stewart
discussed with you.

19:07.374 --> 19:08.934
Yes, but...
James trusts me.

19:08.934 --> 19:10.214
Don't you, James?

19:10.214 --> 19:12.014
Yes.

19:13.214 --> 19:16.414
So, if you could wait outside,
we'll talk in a moment.

19:26.614 --> 19:27.934
Livy.

19:29.254 --> 19:32.734
Excuse me,
I'm meeting Mrs James Bligh here.

19:32.734 --> 19:35.694
I was hoping you might tell me
where I could find her.

19:49.054 --> 19:53.054
Ah, Doctor, a moment, if I may.
Rather not.

19:53.054 --> 19:56.974
There's an issue of some import
I wish to canvass with you, Doctor.

19:56.974 --> 20:01.054
No doubt you saw me arrive earlier
in the Bligh car.

20:01.054 --> 20:02.174
I didn't.

20:02.174 --> 20:05.974
Oh, well, I'm sure
the staff was abuzz

20:05.974 --> 20:08.734
and I would hate the girls to think
I'm somehow above them

20:08.734 --> 20:10.294
after the experience.

20:10.294 --> 20:13.694
Rest assured,
I'm still the same Doris Collins.

20:13.694 --> 20:16.374
I must say, even Norman
seemed a little disconcerted

20:16.374 --> 20:18.774
to be addressed so openly
from the rear seat.

20:18.774 --> 20:21.094
One imagines
he's unused to passengers

20:21.094 --> 20:22.694
bridging the social divide,

20:22.694 --> 20:25.614
but front seat or back,
I'm the same woman.

20:25.614 --> 20:27.014
Doctor?

20:41.414 --> 20:43.854
I was starting to give up on you.
I'm not here to chat.

20:44.894 --> 20:46.054
Please, can't we just...?

20:46.054 --> 20:47.774
What happens if she doesn't want
to know about me?

20:47.774 --> 20:49.214
If she doesn't ask?

20:50.774 --> 20:52.014
Come inside. Let me get you a drink.

20:52.014 --> 20:55.294
I'm teetotal, which you'd know if
you hadn't ignored me for 20 years.

20:55.294 --> 20:57.254
I'm sure she will ask.

20:57.254 --> 21:00.014
If she doesn't,
what will you tell her?

21:00.014 --> 21:01.334
Will you tell her about me anyway?

21:04.134 --> 21:05.254
That's what I thought.

21:05.254 --> 21:07.694
It's not that simple.
She has a father.

21:07.694 --> 21:08.814
Damn right she does! Me!

21:08.814 --> 21:10.974
She comes first.

21:10.974 --> 21:13.494
If she asks, I will tell her,
but if she doesn't...

21:13.494 --> 21:15.214
You made me miss her whole life!

21:16.334 --> 21:19.014
Then you hold her in front of me
and tell me maybe I can't have it.

21:19.014 --> 21:20.334
No, I don't need your permission.

21:20.334 --> 21:22.294
Jack!
You can shove your bloody offer.

21:22.294 --> 21:24.494
Can we just...?
Wherever she is, I'll find her.

21:24.494 --> 21:26.094
I will find her.

21:57.674 --> 22:00.794
You'll be here, of course,
when Sarah arrives.

22:00.794 --> 22:02.594
Naturally.

22:04.154 --> 22:05.234
Naturally.

22:07.074 --> 22:09.474
I think it's best
Anna is left to her own devices,

22:09.474 --> 22:11.234
for a few days at least.

22:11.234 --> 22:12.954
I agree.

22:12.954 --> 22:16.234
I've already taken steps
to quash gossip on both accounts.

22:16.234 --> 22:17.754
Good.

22:17.754 --> 22:20.074
(CLOCK CHIMES)

22:20.074 --> 22:21.234
Well, excuse me.

22:22.754 --> 22:24.474
When did you intend telling me?

22:25.514 --> 22:26.554
What?

22:26.554 --> 22:28.594
About your sister.

22:40.674 --> 22:41.954
George!

22:45.314 --> 22:46.874
Well, if you're here to see Sarah,

22:46.874 --> 22:48.554
you have a strange way
of showing it.

22:48.554 --> 22:50.794
You didn't tell mother, did you?
No, no, no.

22:50.794 --> 22:52.954
I was quick enough on my feet
to cover for you.

22:52.954 --> 22:55.994
Assuming it's Anna you're here for.
Yes.

22:55.994 --> 22:57.754
I should have guessed
with all the trips to the city.

22:57.754 --> 22:59.314
She's been talking to you
about Gino.

22:59.314 --> 23:01.154
You know about him?
I do now.

23:02.474 --> 23:05.514
She needed someone.
I'm glad it was you.

23:06.434 --> 23:08.594
I've been so caught up
in my own problems, I didn't see it.

23:08.594 --> 23:12.114
She loves him.
Yes.

23:12.114 --> 23:13.354
Have you been to the farm?

23:14.634 --> 23:17.954
Mother didn't tell you?
Tell me what?

23:17.954 --> 23:19.954
Anna's living with the Polettis
for three months.

23:19.954 --> 23:22.754
(GASPS) She's...?
We struck a deal.

23:22.754 --> 23:25.834
She's there to get a taste
of married life.

23:25.834 --> 23:28.914
Separate beds, I assume.
Only you would ask that.

23:28.914 --> 23:31.474
If they can make it work,
they have my blessing.

23:31.474 --> 23:33.874
I'm impressed.
It was Sarah's idea.

23:33.874 --> 23:35.594
But you agreed to it.

23:35.594 --> 23:37.154
I like your Sarah.

23:37.154 --> 23:39.234
You'd like her even more
when you meet her.

23:39.234 --> 23:41.554
Being there for Anna's taken
all my attention,

23:41.554 --> 23:43.354
but I promise I will make up for it.

23:45.594 --> 23:49.594
It must be hard sometimes,
being Aunt Carolyn.

23:52.954 --> 23:54.314
It's the price I pay.

24:03.194 --> 24:06.754
What are you doing?
What are YOU doing?

24:06.754 --> 24:10.514
Turns out that a French polish isn't
compatible with doing the dishes.

24:10.514 --> 24:14.074
(SPEAKS ITALIAN)
They're just nails.

24:14.074 --> 24:15.234
Well, they're beautiful.

24:16.434 --> 24:19.314
And I love you for doing this.

24:19.314 --> 24:20.874
Gino!

24:23.434 --> 24:25.754
Gino's kissing Anna!
Hey, get out of here!

24:25.754 --> 24:26.954
Gino's kissing Anna!

24:26.954 --> 24:28.234
Get out of here!
Please get out.

24:28.234 --> 24:29.834
Mamma! Mamma! Gino's kissing Anna!

24:29.834 --> 24:31.314
No, we weren't.

24:31.314 --> 24:34.714
(ALL SPEAK ITALIAN)

24:34.714 --> 24:35.834
I didn't do anything!

24:35.834 --> 24:41.234
(ALL SPEAK ITALIAN)

24:43.834 --> 24:44.874
Sit.

24:49.514 --> 24:52.194
We have one rule - no touching.

24:52.194 --> 24:53.914
You touch, she goes.
Mamma, please...

24:53.914 --> 24:55.354
"Mamma," nothing.

24:55.354 --> 24:57.034
Anna, to the kitchen.

25:02.114 --> 25:03.954
Your papa is right.

25:05.154 --> 25:08.674
A man controls himself.
A decent man.

25:09.914 --> 25:11.314
Hmm?
Si.

25:12.554 --> 25:13.674
Si.

25:27.754 --> 25:29.874
Thought I saw you arrive.

25:29.874 --> 25:32.074
Where's James?
In his treatment.

25:32.074 --> 25:34.154
He has it in the afternoon.

25:34.154 --> 25:35.994
Twice a day now.

25:35.994 --> 25:38.154
That's too much.
Mrs Bligh.

25:38.154 --> 25:40.114
It is too much.

25:41.274 --> 25:43.154
Mrs Bligh, I'm afraid
I'm going to have to ask you

25:43.154 --> 25:44.274
to stay away for a while.

25:44.274 --> 25:45.274
No!

25:45.274 --> 25:48.194
Any progress we make with James, you
undo with your displays of distress.

25:48.194 --> 25:49.354
I don't!

25:49.354 --> 25:51.274
You fret over him,
aggravating his fears,

25:51.274 --> 25:52.834
making treatment nigh on impossible.

25:52.834 --> 25:55.314
You are counter-productive
to his health

25:55.314 --> 25:58.514
and your own,
not to mention the unborn.

26:01.234 --> 26:06.034
Do you want James cured
of this perversion or not?

26:07.034 --> 26:08.274
I...

26:11.954 --> 26:13.714
I want him better.

26:13.714 --> 26:17.594
Then we will review the advisability
of you visiting him in a few weeks.

26:17.594 --> 26:19.514
But Dr Stewart said...

26:19.514 --> 26:21.034
He's in complete agreement.

26:26.034 --> 26:27.354
Excellent.

27:03.994 --> 27:06.194
Not exactly the sort of farewell
I wanted for you.

27:07.234 --> 27:08.474
Me neither.

27:10.434 --> 27:11.994
You look after her, Mr Bligh.

27:13.234 --> 27:15.154
Don't worry. She's in good hands.

27:15.154 --> 27:16.354
(DOG BARKS)

27:16.354 --> 27:18.074
Just like he is.

27:18.074 --> 27:20.594
Looks like you'll have two old dogs
to come visit, eh?

27:32.194 --> 27:33.834
If you can't live with it...

27:33.834 --> 27:35.194
I will.

28:02.034 --> 28:03.274
Good luck, Missy.

28:33.154 --> 28:34.634
Point of no return.

28:36.354 --> 28:37.554
Miss Adams, welcome.

28:37.554 --> 28:39.594
Oh, it was kind of you to meet me,
Mrs Bligh.

28:39.594 --> 28:41.874
The least any guest can expect.

28:41.874 --> 28:44.194
The grey room for Miss Adams,
I think, Amy.

28:44.194 --> 28:45.194
Yes, Mrs Bligh.

28:45.194 --> 28:46.954
Actually, Amy,
Anna offered her room.

28:46.954 --> 28:49.274
It'll be much nicer.
Yes, sir.

28:49.274 --> 28:50.794
But who knows when she'll be back.

28:50.794 --> 28:52.074
No, the grey room, Amy.

28:52.074 --> 28:53.834
Anna's determined
to stay the course.

28:53.834 --> 28:56.194
Best err on the side of caution.

28:56.194 --> 28:58.794
Sarah's more than a guest.
And will be treated accordingly.

28:58.794 --> 29:01.354
The grey room sounds lovely,
thank you.

29:03.634 --> 29:05.554
Um, the grey room?

29:06.874 --> 29:08.114
The grey room.

29:09.874 --> 29:12.274
I can't believe I'm actually here.

29:12.274 --> 29:14.234
I want Ash Park
to feel like your home.

29:15.634 --> 29:17.594
This is home.

29:17.594 --> 29:20.674
It's hardly our most luxurious
accommodation.

29:20.674 --> 29:22.394
I think it's perfect.

29:23.634 --> 29:25.274
Well, don't get too used to it.

29:25.274 --> 29:27.114
In a few months,
you'll be in with me.

29:28.154 --> 29:30.714
Perhaps a guided tour.
Don't tempt me.

29:30.714 --> 29:35.074
I'm here to win over your mother
and that is not the way to do it.

29:45.194 --> 29:47.194
(KNOCK AT DOOR)
I'm busy.

29:47.194 --> 29:48.554
We need you in the ward.

29:48.554 --> 29:50.914
(DOOR RATTLES)
I'm coming!

29:50.914 --> 29:52.714
It's urgent, Doctor.

30:04.055 --> 30:07.815
(BOTH SPEAK ITALIAN)

30:13.255 --> 30:15.735
AMO: Miss Carolyn!
Sorry to drop in unannounced.

30:17.175 --> 30:18.815
So many years, we no see you.

30:18.815 --> 30:21.175
How beautiful you are
and still so young.

30:21.175 --> 30:22.895
Oh, you make me blush!

30:22.895 --> 30:24.695
Look at you, madam!
What a difference.

30:24.695 --> 30:27.615
And all worth it. This is Gino.

30:27.615 --> 30:30.815
Course it is.
The pleasure is all mine.

30:30.815 --> 30:33.695
We make coffee. Real Italian coffee.
You like?

30:33.695 --> 30:36.055
I love.
We'll bring it to you. Anna.

30:37.695 --> 30:39.175
It's nice to meet you...

30:39.175 --> 30:40.535
(WHISPERS) ..Mamma.

30:42.055 --> 30:46.095
He knows?
Everything. You can trust him.

30:46.095 --> 30:47.575
What do you think?

30:49.255 --> 30:51.375
Gorgeous.

30:51.375 --> 30:54.735
And he loves you, so rather special.

30:56.815 --> 30:58.415
I'm happy it worked out.

30:58.415 --> 31:00.015
Me too.

31:01.015 --> 31:03.175
What's that look for, then?

31:03.175 --> 31:04.895
Father was here yesterday.

31:06.055 --> 31:08.375
I couldn't tell him that I know.

31:08.375 --> 31:10.255
He was so sweet.

31:10.255 --> 31:14.415
You don't have to say anything.
Not yet. Not ever, if you prefer.

31:14.415 --> 31:17.215
You're my mother.
I want everyone to know.

31:17.215 --> 31:19.895
In time. This first.

31:20.975 --> 31:23.415
Do you think George will be hurt?

31:23.415 --> 31:26.095
He is still your father.
But he won't be.

31:26.095 --> 31:27.855
No.

31:31.255 --> 31:34.895
And your real father?
You're not curious?

31:34.895 --> 31:36.255
Of course.

31:38.695 --> 31:40.455
It's complex enough already.

31:57.095 --> 31:58.575
JAMES: Hey.

32:02.535 --> 32:05.375
You're back with us.
You're doing very well, James.

32:05.375 --> 32:08.615
Where...where's Livy?

32:08.615 --> 32:11.455
Mrs Bligh won't be with us
for some time.

32:12.375 --> 32:16.055
Thought it best that you have
some peace and quiet to recover

32:16.055 --> 32:18.735
and to allow the treatment
the best chance of success.

32:19.815 --> 32:21.295
It's what you want, isn't it?

32:22.535 --> 32:24.615
To enjoy your wife and your family

32:24.615 --> 32:26.535
without the spectre of perversion
hovering?

32:26.535 --> 32:28.335
My head hurts.

32:28.335 --> 32:32.695
We're making you better
and that's what we want.

32:32.695 --> 32:33.695
Yes?

32:40.615 --> 32:43.175
We're on voltage two at the moment.
We'll take it up to five.

33:38.615 --> 33:40.775
WOMAN: Just down here to the right,
Mr Richards.

34:26.895 --> 34:29.895
Oh, Miss Adams! More than punctual.

34:29.895 --> 34:32.135
I hoped we might talk before dinner.

34:34.614 --> 34:36.054
I come in peace.

34:37.614 --> 34:40.614
We both know that you'll try
to stop this marriage

34:40.614 --> 34:42.534
and we also know
I'm not about to let you.

34:43.735 --> 34:45.815
So, this is your line
drawn in the sand?

34:45.815 --> 34:49.094
More our Geneva Convention.
Oh, your rules of engagement.

34:49.094 --> 34:50.255
A rule.

34:51.895 --> 34:54.614
Whatever blows we land,
we leave George out of it.

34:55.695 --> 34:58.895
We both love him.
We don't want him hurt.

34:58.895 --> 35:00.055
Agreed.

35:00.055 --> 35:01.335
Thank you.

35:01.335 --> 35:03.695
Although we did make an agreement
once before.

35:03.695 --> 35:05.735
James.
Yes.

35:07.015 --> 35:08.895
Break this one at your peril.

35:09.975 --> 35:13.695
Sherry?
Thank you.

35:16.615 --> 35:20.255
Anna should do that.
Ma, she's tired.

35:20.255 --> 35:24.215
A farmer's wife doesn't rest
so SHE doesn't rest.

35:24.215 --> 35:25.815
Ma!

35:47.855 --> 35:49.095
(WHISPERS) Ma...

35:50.255 --> 35:51.655
..let her sleep.

35:51.655 --> 35:53.095
Tonight.

35:54.175 --> 35:55.535
Tomorrow, dishes.

36:03.375 --> 36:05.135
Now, I hope you won't mind

36:05.135 --> 36:08.015
if I leave you both alone
for a few days.

36:08.015 --> 36:09.055
Where are you going?

36:09.055 --> 36:11.015
I'd like to visit James and Olivia

36:11.015 --> 36:13.335
so I intend to leave
on Sunday after Matins,

36:13.335 --> 36:14.855
unless you have any objections.

36:14.855 --> 36:16.695
No, no. By all means.

36:16.695 --> 36:19.655
I thought not.
It's not your heart, is it?

36:19.655 --> 36:21.975
Oh, don't be so dramatic, George.

36:21.975 --> 36:24.655
Although I do intend
to see my specialist.

36:24.655 --> 36:27.175
I thought Miss Adams might like
the chance to settle in,

36:27.175 --> 36:28.535
to adjust.

36:28.535 --> 36:30.095
That's very thoughtful.

36:31.775 --> 36:33.255
Well, it's been a long day.

36:33.255 --> 36:34.415
If you'll excuse me.

36:36.015 --> 36:37.935
Goodnight, Miss Adams.
Goodnight.

36:37.935 --> 36:39.535
Goodnight, mother.
Goodnight, George.

36:45.135 --> 36:46.975
That's the last thing I expected.

37:00.855 --> 37:02.775
Yes, I'd like to make
a long-distance call

37:02.775 --> 37:04.775
to Sydney, please, Mildred.

37:04.775 --> 37:06.175
To the Australia Hotel.

37:07.895 --> 37:08.935
Mm-hm.

37:08.935 --> 37:13.655
And I want to speak to a guest,
Mrs Regina Standish.

37:15.295 --> 37:17.495
There are things I haven't told you.

37:19.375 --> 37:23.055
Mother has reason
to be concerned about James.

37:25.215 --> 37:28.295
Best you settle before I burden you
with family problems.

37:28.295 --> 37:31.015
When it's right.
Soon.

37:32.735 --> 37:35.855
And then, no secrets between us...

37:36.855 --> 37:37.975
..ever.

37:44.575 --> 37:46.935
I had to lie.

37:46.935 --> 37:49.055
I had no choice.

37:52.775 --> 37:54.935
That's enough for today.
It's getting late.

37:56.575 --> 37:58.655
So many secrets.

37:59.935 --> 38:03.375
Did you finally tell him?
Never about the murder.

38:05.335 --> 38:07.975
Other secrets refused
to stay silent.

38:09.735 --> 38:11.935
Even some I didn't know myself.

38:25.039 --> 38:28.239
Bye, Samantha.
Bye, Leah. Thank you.

38:31.599 --> 38:33.639
She told me
something extraordinary...

38:34.799 --> 38:36.039
..in confidence.

38:36.039 --> 38:38.479
She's led an extraordinary life.

38:39.799 --> 38:41.959
Just hope my book
can do her justice.

38:41.959 --> 38:42.999
See you.

38:51.479 --> 38:55.879
(CLASSICAL MUSIC PLAYS ON RADIO)

38:58.759 --> 39:00.679
(HORN HONKS)

39:11.039 --> 39:12.999
(HORSES HOOVES APPROACH)

40:02.479 --> 40:03.599
Turn it off.

40:03.599 --> 40:05.399
Turn it off!

40:09.879 --> 40:11.439
Turn it off!
What is it?

40:13.039 --> 40:14.679
(MUSIC STOPS)

40:14.679 --> 40:16.959
We had no choice.

40:16.959 --> 40:20.839
It was him or them.
Who? Sarah?

40:22.599 --> 40:24.319
It was him or them.

40:24.319 --> 40:26.039
WOMAN: Please, Bert.
Louise needs you.

40:26.039 --> 40:29.759
Don't touch me! Don't you touch me!

40:29.759 --> 40:31.239
Look what you made me do.
Oh, please!

40:31.239 --> 40:33.039
Why would I stay with you?
Why would I stay?

40:33.039 --> 40:34.799
Please!
Look at what you made me do.

40:34.799 --> 40:36.519
Please, Bert, please!
Just shut up!

40:36.519 --> 40:38.599
Just shut up.

40:38.599 --> 40:40.479
Look at what you made me do.

40:40.479 --> 40:42.599
Please!
Look at this.

40:42.599 --> 40:44.039
Look at what you made me do!

41:05.519 --> 41:07.599
(BABY CRIES)
Bert!

41:07.599 --> 41:09.239
Bert!

41:11.959 --> 41:15.159
What have you done?
Colin, what have you done?

41:17.679 --> 41:20.679
What have you done? Colin?

41:20.679 --> 41:22.519
(HORSE WHINNIES)

41:25.759 --> 41:26.959
Come on!

41:26.959 --> 41:28.919
Oh, no.

41:35.879 --> 41:37.319
No secrets.

41:39.879 --> 41:41.719
Ever.

41:52.999 --> 41:53.999
We had a child.

41:53.999 --> 41:59.239
Not knowing for so many years
would break your heart.

41:59.239 --> 42:00.679
You made me miss her whole life!

42:02.239 --> 42:04.479
There are reasons.

42:04.479 --> 42:06.559
It's my right to know her.
I can't.

42:06.559 --> 42:09.519
She's closer than he ever imagined.

42:10.239 --> 42:11.759
You're still my little girl.

42:11.759 --> 42:15.679
How can I help you
if you won't tell me? Tell me.

42:15.679 --> 42:18.919
When he finds out who she is...

42:18.919 --> 42:20.279
I deserve more.

42:20.279 --> 42:23.879
..it'll be the most confronting
moment of his life.

42:23.879 --> 42:26.079
Please, tell me.

